9 g. Standardized test fees and advanced placement examinations or examinations
10 related to postsecondary education admission or credentialing;
11 h. Tuition or fees for dual-credit courses;
12 i. Meals served to students in school buildings;
13 j. Mental health assistance;
14 k. Medical appointments necessary for educational benefit;
15 l. Educational camps; and
16 m. Qualified expenses as adopted by the superintendent of public instruction in
17 administrative rules.
18 Education savings account fund - Establishment - Continuing appropriation .
19 There is created in the state treasury an education savings account fund. The fund consists
20 of moneys appropriated to the superintendent of public instruction for the education savings
21 account program. Moneys in the fund are appropriated on a continuing basis for education
22 savings accounts.
23 Superintendent of public instruction - Administrator - Duties.
24 1. The superintendent of public instruction is the education savings account program
25 administrator, and shall:
26 a. Annually inform eligible students and parents of the schools participating in the
27 education savings account program;
28 b. Create a standard application form a parent of an eligible student may submit to
29 establish the student's eligibility for the education savings account program. The
30 superintendent shall ensure the application is readily available to interested
31 families through various sources, including the department's website;
