2 savings account payment for the eligible studen t , if known at the time of the notice .
3 3. For an eligible studen t approved for an education savings account payment, the
4 superintenden t of public instruction or third-party entity shall establish an individua l
5 account for the eligible studen t in the education savings account fund and deposit the
6 payment into the eligible studen t 's individual account within thirty days following
7 submission of the application, but in any case no later than July fifteenth. The funds
8 must be available immediately for the payment of qualified educational expenses
9 incurred by the parent for the eligible studen t during the fiscal year .
10 4. A nonpublic school or other provider of qualified educational expenses accepting
11 payment from a parent using funds from an eligible studen t 's individual account in the
12 fund may not refund, rebate, or share any portion of the payment with the parent or
13 eligible studen t .
14 5. Moneys remaining in an eligible studen t 's individual account upon conclusion of the
15 fiscal year must be returned to the education savings account fund.
16 6. Beginning with the school budget year beginning July 1, 2026, for each school year ,
17 an eligible studen t who :
18 a. Attends a public school is eligible to receive an education savings account
19 payment of one thousand dollars.
20 b. Is enrolled in and attends a nonpublic participating school is eligible to receive an
21 education savings account payment of:
22 (1) Four thousand dollars, if the eligible studen t 's household has an annua l
23 income less than or equal to two hundred percent of the most recently
24 revised poverty income guidelines published by the United States
25 department of health and human services.
26 (2) Two thousand five hundred dollars, if the eligible studen t 's household has
27 an annual income less than or equal to four hundred percent of the most
28 recently revised poverty income guidelines published by the United States
29 department of health and human services.
30 (3) One thousand dollars, if the eligible studen t does not qualify under
31 paragraph 1 or 2 .
