1 c. Participates in a home education program in accordance with chapter 15.1 - 23, is
2 eligible to receive an education savings account payment of one thousand
3 dollars.
4 7. Education savings account payments may be approved for one school year and
5 applications must be submitted annually for payments in subsequent school years.
6 8. Funds deposited in an education savings account are not taxable income to the parent
7 or eligible studen t .
8 Participating schools - Accountability standards.
9 1. A participating school shall:
10 a. Comply with all health and safety laws or codes that apply to nonpublic schools .
11 b. Hold a valid occupancy permit if required by the city in which the school is
12 located.
13 c. Certify the school complies with the nondiscrimination policies under 42 U.S.C .
14 1981.
15 d. Conduct criminal background checks on employees.
16 e. Exclude from employment any individual who:
17 (1) Is not permitted by state law to work in a nonpublic school; or
18 (2) Might reasonably pose a threat to the safety of eligible studen t s .
19 f. Provide a parent with a receipt for all qualifying expenses at the school.
20 g. Demonstrate the school's financial viability, if the school will receive fifty thousand
21 dollars or more during the school year, by filing with the superintendent of public
22 instruction before the start of the school year:
23 (1) A surety bond payable to the state in an amount equal to the aggregate
24 amount of funds from education savings accounts the participating school
25 expects to receive; or
26 (2) Financial information demonstrating the school is able to pay an aggregate
27 amount equal to the amount of the funds from education savings accounts
28 the participating school expects to receive.
29 2. a. An eligible studen t using education savings account program funds for tuition
30 payments at a participating school shall take required state tests and
31 assessments in accordance with section 15.1 - 21 - 08 .
